main event: Six white objects were seen by a weather observer following a path similar to a balloon release in Knoxville, Tennessee on October 20, 1952.
interesting points: The objects were observed using a theodolite, a standard weather instrument.
The observed objects were similar to other observations in the project's files.
The objects were seen for 1-2 minutes, following a straight course.
The report notes that the objects were possibly a balloon, but does not provide a definitive conclusion.
The report is part of Project Blue Book, a U.S. Air Force program to investigate unidentified flying objects.
